      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">Here's hoping that they find a happy medium between TBC and Wrath -- Wrath was too easy, while TBC was too hard to meet the requirements for your first few heroics. <br /> <br />I remember lots and lots and lots and lots of Normal dungeons just to meet the minimum requirements to even get into the easier heroic dungeons in TBC; but then nobody (who had came and geared up before me) wanted normals because they didn't get anything out of them. <br /> <br />In Wrath, anyone with the starting blues could easily clear most of the non-FH heroics, but the dungeons themselves required little thought or skill (the occasional gimmick fight, but nothing really challenging). <br /> <br />In Cata, what I'd like to see is TBC-style dungeons, but yet Wrath's system of allowing people to perform in those heroics after a modest amount of gear-gathering (full set of craftables allowing one to be almost-heroic-ready). <br /> <br />For those players of lesser skill (or those who don't have time to farm up money for those craftable BoEs), they could grind normals a little for a few upgrades before getting into their first heroics. <br /> <br />That'd be the best way to do it IMO. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sep 22nd 2010  3:59pm by Lyrailis </span></i></div>
      <div class="msgFtFrame"><div class="msgFtFrameFix"></div><div class="msgReplies"><a href="javascript:scrollTo(0,0);">&#9650; Page top</a> |   <a href="/forum.html?forum=21&amp;mid=128518497616643769&amp;page=1&amp;howmany=50#msg1285185489177988912" class="icon-linktothis" rel="nofollow">Link to this post</a>  </div></div>
