      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName " href="/users/TallusRip">TallusRip</a></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/></div><div class="msgWhoNum">61 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Decent  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">It'd be nice if they were at least a little more challenging than Wrath's current Heroics, but not as bad as TBC (and God help us if Blizzard makes instances super-huge again.)  At least, speaking from a healing point of view.  I've been doing random TBC instances with my druid lately, and no matter how often I tell people to try avoiding the bombs in Blood Furnace, DPS ignore me, the Tank doesn't move the mobs, and it's a fight to keep them all alive.  Clothies die super fast....there've been a few times where I've started casting Regrowth on the tank, and a cloth dps starts taking damage and is dead before it finishes.  It's ridiculous.  Part of me wonders if I could heal better, but another part wonders why caster DPS is standing that close to the mobs/bombs anyway. <br /> <br />I'd say a happy medium, too, would be if Heroics had more than just a level requirement.  In TBC you had to farm rep to get Keys to the Heroic versions of the instances.  I'd hardly say someone ought to be Exalted with a difficult-to-get faction (there's only so many times I'll run an instance for ANYTHING before I start to wonder why I'm <i>paying</i> Blizzard to do something I hate), but maybe Revered...something high enough where you need to have learned the instances and had the chances to get the gear while there. <br /> <br />Gearscore also needs to be removed from the game, or at least the Blizzard version of it.  There's been a few occasions where a dual-spec player will enter an instance with great gear for one spec, but then switch to the other and need to be carried.  Blizzard's gear-checker thing only recognizes your highest gear value to date, not what you have on at the moment.  If the dungeons kicked players for no longer meeting gear requirements, then I may take back the need to remove the system.  It's especially important for healers and tanks to be able to do their jobs effectively in a difficult instance.  The second they're under-geared, they are under-prepared to do that job.  HP and MP pools disintegrate, and the chances for wiping go way up.  It's frustrating.  Many times have I loathed to remain in an HHoR group that turns out to have a barely-4k GS Tank, only to leave in the middle of an obvious wipe before imminent death...although I'll always give teams that stick around past the doorway a chance to finish.  I hate leaving before we're done, but dammit, I hate paying unnecessary repair bills, too. <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />TL;DR: Bring back rep requirements for Heroic keys.  Remove Blizzard's gear value system for entering dungeons, or edit the system so as to kick players who swap specs/gear and no longer meet instance requirements.</div>
