      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">ElMuneco wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">TallusRip wrote:</div><div class="orig"> <br />TL;DR: Bring back rep requirements for Heroic keys.  Remove Blizzard's gear value system for entering dungeons, or edit the system so as to kick players who swap specs/gear and no longer meet instance requirements.</div></div> <br />I admire the sentiment.  The nerfed BC rep requirement (Honored instead of Revered) would be fine with me, especially if it was more balanced toward dungeons and away from questing.</div></div> <br /> <br />We don't need restrictions/attunements. <br /> <br />I didn't like the BC requirements, because it required a bunch of stupid quest and normal instance grinding just to get in the dungeons, and each dungeon cluster had its own rep. You could be geared out the wazoo, able to clear Kara, but yet be forbidden to enter (insert cluster here) because you were short on some rep. <br /> <br />Maybe if you had a &quot;One Rep Fits All&quot;, maybe. <br /> <br />But, if you require everyone to do Normals to get into Heroics, we'd have a repeat of TBC, where a newcomer who's &quot;Late to the Party&quot;, you end up with a similar situation: Sitting in LFD for 30min+ trying to get a dungeon. <br /> <br />That is just not fun at all, in the least. Nobody should be punished for arriving late, and/or trying to gear up an alt. <br /> <br />Wrath's system is fine -- they just needed the dungeons to be a little harder, and more thought-provoking instead of &quot;LOL AOE GOGOGOGOGO&quot;. <br /> <br />Heroics should be possible with a decent amount of challenge in near-full BoE endgame gear, with enchants/gems. The catch, is that proper play mechanics need to be used, or you will die. You'd need CCs, Support Tactics, and you'd need to use the boss's mechanics the way they were meant to be used, to have a hope of winning the fight. <br /> <br />Whether or not you can clear the first batch of Heroic instances should <b>never</b> based upon gear. It should be based upon <u>skill</u>. Requiring you to grind reputation isn't skill. Requiring you to clear easy versions of said dungeon 100x to gear up, isn't skill. Its redundancy and repetition. <br /> <br />The only thing I would support, maybe, maybe, is having the requirement of the achievement for clearing the normal version of said dungeon before you're permitted to Q up for the heroic version. Maybe. Until/unless it becomes a bottleneck, where people can't get into dungeons because they still need a normal version clear, then I dunno. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sep 22nd 2010  8:04pm by Lyrailis </span></i></div>
