      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">Whether or not you can clear the first batch of Heroic instances should never based upon gear. It should be based upon skill.</div></div> <br /> <br />Clearing content is <b>always</b> based on gear.  The expectation is that the requirement is reasonable.  You probably won't be able to clear each level 85 dungeon once and then move on to heroics.  You may need a full set of level 83-85 blues, especially right away when everyone will have to contribute for a group to succeed, and that's reasonable.  People are way to used to current dungeons where a decked out tank and a healer can duo the whole thing. <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">Heroics should be possible with a decent amount of challenge in near-full BoE endgame gear, with enchants/gems</div></div> <br /> <br />Odds are you won't be able to buy a whole set right away.  It will be pricey, and the market won't be saturated.  Gems and enchants will also be very pricey and, unless you get drops from regular dungeons, you will be wearing quested gear.  Who wants to put over priced enchants on quested blues? <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig"> Requiring you to grind reputation isn't skill. Requiring you to clear easy versions of said dungeon 100x to gear up, isn't skill. Its redundancy and repetition.</div></div> <br /> <br />Rep grind isn't the way to go but it's fine if you have to run the *gasp* regular dungeons a few times to get some gear.  Repeatedly running random heroics in LK is very easy, yet it's the way virtually everyone gears up.  From the looks of it, regular level 85 dungeons will require more advanced tactics and have more engaging mechanics than most LK heroics anyway.  If the content is fun, which I expect it to be, I have no problem running a beautiful dungeon like Throne of Tides a few times for a nice level 85 blue that would serve me well while running heroics.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Homer no function beer well without.</div></div>
