      <div class="msgContentFrame">Hmm, yeah, I want them to be challenging, but I also want them to be puggable.  I remember wiping wayyy too many times in pugs near the beginning of Wrath in VH, Nexus, etc  (I really don't want to talk about my first night in Wrath, and the number of drunk hours we spent in UK normal lol).  It's likely some of the people in those pugs were undergeared for them, sure, and I guess that nowdays I have an easier time of saying, screw this, I'm done, so I probably won't waste as much time as I used to in heroic pugs.  I guess it will always be that way, though, because some people have no idea that they should move out of dangerous-looking stuff.  It's a good thing they put in at least some gear requirements for heroics, though, I guess.  I'm sure it will be easier to go in with guildies, but I DO still enjoy pugging and meeting new people outside of my guild. <br /> <br />Anyway, that video was fun to watch, but definitely makes me not want to pug anything for a while.  I'll stick with guildies.  I haven't had THE worst luck of pugs not wanting to wipe and work on things, but the reality is that a lot of pugs will just leave without trying, so you have the revolving door thing going on, which bugs the hell out of me (unless it's obvious that it's just not gonna happen, I grok that). <br /> <br />I'm kind of feverish and rambling right now, but I just hope it doesn't take TOO many wipes and heroic farming to get ready to raid.  I'm fine with some, and I don't want to roflstomp all the heroics at first glance, but heroics, for me, are the means to an end.  I want to raid ASAP and that's what I want to spend most of my time on. <br /> <br />I do remember some Wrath heroics that I pugged that weren't stupid simple, in that the mechanics could wipe us quickly: <br />UK: hide behind the posts for the last boss <br />UP: omg who's getting the harpoons?? <br />HOL: what's that debuff mean? <br />VH: purple orbs are coming at me, help? <br /> <br />I know that right now it's easy to carry your friends or some doofus who is clueless, but it wasn't so easy at the beginning if you weren't going in with sunwell or w/e gear.  I might not have any hair left if the LFD tool was around back then.  :) <br /> <br />I guess what I -really- want is for the heroics to be difficult and challenging, but I want all the puggers to be good at learning from mistakes.  Too much to ask?  Sigh, thought so.  :)<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>&quot;could u guys pls tell me how to do herbalism on dead monster?&quot;</div></div>
