      <div class="msgContentFrame">I just tried my first heroic on beta, with premade characters.  It was Halls of Origination. <br />The first boss has a neat mechanic where he goes immune, and two DPS have to hop down, aoe a couple of snakes, and pull a lever to shut off his shield.  VERY fun in normal. <br />On heroic, you hop down (His shield does damage, hop QUICK), and try to aoe a snake, and get one shot by a snake with 70K HP.  We tried a strategy where we hop down, let the healer bomb a big heal on us, then the tank waits up top to grab the snakes when they aggro the healer.  We then pull the lever.  Problem is, we're still getting one shot as soon as the snakes see us.  We tried taking the whole group down, pulling one switch, and plopping over, but it just didn't work. <br />It's very possible that it's overtuned or just plain broken at the moment.  The trash hit HARD, and required CC, but wasn't terrible like the boss.  I will say that if you charge in trying to AoE every pull down, the tank will die and the healer will OOM.  CC is NECESSARY, but only one to two mobs at a time.  There's also obvious AoE packs of non elites (General Cata rule: If it's non elite, there's more to grab and aoe). <br /> <br />Broken, but I can see once they tune it they'll be challenging but not impossible.  Of course, when we're wearing full T13, they'll be a joke, but, they're entry content.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Druid-Wakayaja||Paladin-Zavo||Warrior-Drest||Mage-Versi||Shaman-Kuroderm||Hunter-Fiagai||Death Knight-Zavoyevatd|| <br />^Sisters of Elune^ <br />Rogue-Nalgas||Priest-Sacerdot|| <br />^Cenarian Circle^ <br />1983 Mazda RX7 GSL - Rexie - My Garage <br /> <br />&quot;Saying that a druid can go resto and do well in arena and saying that a hunter can't do the same doesn't make any sense whatsoever.&quot; - Wait. . . what?</div></div>
