      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">My thoughts: <br /> <br />I like that the encounters are difficult. There seems to be a problem with the current system when you run a totally random heroic and you can clear it in 15 minutes.  <br /> <br />I think that the first error Blizzard had was making FULL T9(10) open to any random schmuck. Don't get me wrong, I love how quickly you can gear up now, it's certainly a time saver, but what it also shows is that you don't have to be a good player to get it.  <br /> <br />I took great pride that, given how my guild generally sucked at raids during BC (I stayed because the I liked the people in it, and wanted to have fun), that I had an &quot;Epic&quot; mage at the end of it. I wasn't a DPS God, but because I started with blues and greens (I was doing 400 DPS during this time) and moved up through months of pain, I felt very accomplished. Now, someone can get, all things being equal, BETTER gear in the span of a weekend.  <br /> <br />In the YouTube video that was posted, I will grant that it was hard as hell, but I think we're all just a little spoiled right now from how easy heroics have become. Anybody remember H CoS? It was a bit of a nightmare at first, and I'm not talking about finding the grain, listening to Arthas and Uther blab, etc. What I mean is that it was a big deal to be able to get to the boss to get a shot at the drake. Now it's a given.  <br /> <br />There's also a major problem of groups totally collapsing when, God forbid, the group wipes. I laugh at this. Wipes were just parts of life in BC. It didn't mean you sucked, it meant that you were in a tough fight. <br /> <br />I've found that this growth in entitlement and sheer impatience is disturbing. Maybe this might sound like the ramblings of some senile old man, but I worked my ass off to get my gear during BC, damnit, and I was thankful!  <br /> <br />I remember being upset when they moved the requirements for a heroic key from being revered to honored. Even though I benefited from it (Yes, living in Tempest Keep and the Caverns of Time sucked, I'll admit), people simply were not ready at that point to go into heroics. &quot;Oh, I'm 70, I've got my key, I'm going into Heroic Ramparts!&quot;. Let me tell you something. I was one of those people. My group got it's ass KICKED. It was such a step up from something like Shadow Labs or Bot, and I quickly learned that I had to bring my A game. I became a better player as a result of it.  <br /> <br />Now, if I was upset when Blizzard did that (as well as removing being keyed for raids), I was probably on the verge of having a stroke when they decided to potentially let any random Joe into a HEROIC dungeon or a Raid, and the players suffered as a result. They thought they were automatically ready for that kind of action, when the truth is they weren't.  <br /> <br />The first heroic I tanked was Nexus. It was a major failure. We died on that mage too many times to remember, and we kept getting murdered by the final boss &quot;LEARN TO TANK NUB&quot; was the reaction, but was this my fault? The dragon was killing me FIRST, and because suddenly there is no tank to hold the aggro and soak damage, everyone dies. It's not bad tanking, and it wasn't the healing. It was bad DPS. How do I know this? Simple. If you're doing 600 DPS on a boss (at level 80), and when you wipe, the damn thing only has 1400 health left, then yeah, I'd say that's a case of not enough DPS. So, thanks largely to the lack of effort from either a crappy player or a player with crappy gear, or both, I endured four hours of hell. Granted, this is an extreme case, but I'm sure I'm not the only one that has had something like this happen.  <br /> <br />And on being 80, let me tell you something. Before T9(10) came out on my tank (this was before Ulduar, even), I knew that I was going to have to gear up like crazy to stand a chance in Naxx. So, I made a list of all the gear that I needed, and set out getting it. The Naxx run was not perfect by any measurable degree, but we cleared it as a guild for the first time, and I had a tremendous sense of pride that I was the tank.  <br /> <br />So now, we're on the verge of a new expansion. What do we know about it? Well, the days of AoEing the living piss out of anything that moves are long gone. CC is going to be important again (and for those of you that have no idea what that is, that is CROWD CONTROL. Sap, Polymorph, Shackle, Ice Trap, Charm, stuff you never consider touching in a dungeon) thankfully, and there's going to be more of an emphasis on single target damage (Hurray! I love this as I feel that anybody can just AoE the hell out of something and give themselves a nice pat on the back, but it's the single target DPS that shows you just what they bring to the table).  <br /> <br />The thing is, these dungeons are hard now on Beta, and I'll grant that some people are concerned about the diffuculty. Yes, it's going to be hard, but let's look at it a little objectively. People have no clue what they're walking in to, they do not have the benefit of something like DBM to tell them what the boss is about to do, or where you should focus your fire, etc. And in the YouTube video, they admit that they are undergeared.  <br /> <br />Maybe people are overreacting to this. The group clearing ICC in all Blues is a crazy example to show that it's not always about gear, and my hat's off to them, that's a hell of an occasion. Now let's see them try it totally blind, No add-ons, no vent.  <br /> <br />So, I suppose the real question is going to be how easy gear is going to be to receive when you're a level 85. I was not happy that in Wrath you didn't have something that was comparable to the old Dungeon sets, so I can only hope that we'll see D4 and D5 in Cataclysm.  <br /> <br />My final thoughts are that it's nice to see that the game is returning to its roots. I'm looking forward to these alleged nightmares once I hit level 85, because for me that's what makes WoW fun. I don't like how easy it is to just steamroll through encounters in heroics, I feel insulted as a veteran of TBC. Cataclysm is going to be awesome for me, not because it's an expansion, not because of new abilities, or a revamped talent system, and not because of new race and class combos. It's going to be awesome because it's going to be challenging, and that's what I enjoy about this game.  <br /> <br />TL:DR version:  <br /> <br />Enjoy it while it lasts, suckers. You're in for a world of hurt. Me, I'm going to love all of it :D . <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Bladefist&amp;n=Sominus" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Bladefist&amp;n=Sominus">Sominus</a> - 80 Death Knight (Bladefist) <br /><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Bladefist&amp;n=Khalima" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Bladefist&amp;n=Khalima">Khalima</a> - 80 Mage (Bladefist) <br /><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Bladefist&amp;n=Belloq" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Bladefist&amp;n=Belloq">Belloq</a> - 73 Priest (Bladefist) <br /><a href="HTTP://img822.imageshack.us/img822/9571/wowscrnshot082510073418.jpg" rel="external nofollow" title="img822.imageshack.us/img822/9571/wowscrnshot082510073418.jpg">Current UI as of 8/25/10</a></div></div>
