      <div class="msgContentFrame">I've seen two non-heroics from TotalBiscuit (youtube), they look fine. <br /> <br />At least we are back to mobs that have strong abilities that you have to counter instead of just target dummies that you pull, collapse, aoe and loot, and then repeat the process for the rest of the run while completely ignoring what those mobs actually do. <br /> <br />One thing that I find absurd from Wotlk trash mobs is that they don't have any ability worth countering, while even in vanilla as low as Zul Farrak you had mobs that Hex you which you had to dispell and Blooddrinkers that healed from doing a cleave so you had to work around it to avoid healing it more than you're hurting it. <br /> <br />In wotlk mobs that heal are trivial to outdps, and mobs that DPS are trivial to outheal, and they don't seem to have any meaningful ability that does something different than X amount of damage in X form. There's like barely 1 mob in pit of saron which you have to interrupt so that he doesn't Hellfire your entire team, he is trivial to interrupt -or- move away from (he uses the same Hellfire as warlocks and kills himself) and people just wipe because they just don't. <br /> <br />The problem with H HoR isn't so much the instance itself but that people are used to doing the Trivials and want to play H HoR the same way the play the Trivials. <br /> <br />This is my one-button-does-entire-trash-duties-for-the-entire-heroic on my warlock: <br /><pre>/cast [target=mouseover,harm]Seed of Corruption;Rain of Fire</pre> <br />It's a PvP char, it has a bunch of PvP related buttons at the ready, pet switching, mobility, teleportations, snares, CCs, but I don't get to press those unless I pull aggro, which I do because I can solo the pulls anyway. Sometimes I wish there was less retarded immunities on mobs so that I could solo the entire runs and have more fun because I'd use all my buttons instead of -LITERALLY- only one button. <br /> <br />(Note: I don't want it to sound like bragging, I'm trying to describe the level of trivality of wotlk heroics as best I can with examples and experiences and how I feel about it). <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sep 23rd 2010  8:52pm by xorq </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>NOTE: I may post comments about my like/dislike/approval/disapproval of game features. <br />1- They are NOT a complaint. They are a perspective. <br />2- They are NOT advocacy. They are a perspective.</div></div>
