      <div class="msgContentFrame">One other thing that needs to be said to people worried these dungeons might be too hard.  This isn't like hitting level 20 and seeing your first instance.  I get that some people may not have partied once 1-85, but those SHOULD be the exception, not the rule (doubly so with the LFG tool now).  This means they have been learning how parties work and how boss mechanics work the entire time.  The majority of players are also going to have played WOTLK heroics.  This means it is reasonable to assume they have at least that level of skill (no need to specify what level of skill that is.)  If we reset the difficulty again, not only is it suggesting that the majority of the player base can't learn from past experience, it also breaks immersion to a degree. <br /> <br />That's right, I said immersion in an MMO.  I was deeply bothered when I got into WOTLK heroics.  I remember epic struggles getting down some of the BC heroics (well, they seemed epic...it was a long time ago, so no clue now) and now that I'm facing things that are supposed to be an even greater threat, I'm sitting there AoEing everything and barely paying attention.  It felt a little like a joke.  And the word &quot;heroic&quot; quickly lost all meaning.  I went from epic hero fighting off terrible villains to bored soldier who has knows how to pull the trigger on their shiny new toy that blows sh*t up.  So, if we see a bit of a struggle again, I welcome it.  Honestly, much of what I'm hearing about Cata makes me think of FFXI, but ya know, fun, in that it is really trying to give the game a sense of epicness again.  If they add all these cutscenes, make a point on how these things we fight are destroying the world itself, and I can kill them in my sleep, kinda kills the mood...<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Behold the power of procrasti</div></div>
