      <div class="msgContentFrame">I guess my main thing is this: <br /> <br />Will a character be able to _progress_ from Normals, not counting the Boss Drops? <br /> <br />When people say &quot;Normal&quot; and &quot;Heroic Dungeon&quot;, I remember TBC. <br /> <br />My first Level 70 was a Prot Warrior, and I was learning. I got to where I could reliably tank Slabs and CoT: Swamp of Sorrows. <br /> <br />I killed Murmur _8 times_ and never saw his shoulders. Pre-LFD, getting an Slabs run was difficult at best. The only people who'd take me, was my guild, because <i>nobody wanted to do normal dungeons</i> and the only reason my guild offered, is because I was 1 of 3 people who were remotely close to starting Karazhan (this is a guild who was trying to start raiding at the time). <br /> <br />Are we going to get the same thing in Cataclysm? <br /> <br />Tanks having to run Normals 8, 10, 20 times trying for one stinking item that will just not drop no matter what, before they can get the recommended i333 or whatever it is? <br /> <br />That's the main thing about &quot;Heroics&quot;. They drop badges, allowing you to collect them and have 100% chance of getting an item eventually, without having to rely upon boss drops (and getting ninja'd by DPS who live to roll on tank items for an &quot;off-set&quot;). <br /> <br />I am aware there's something called &quot;Justice Points&quot;.... will Normals give Justice Points too? has that been confirmed? <br /> <br />If so, then I wouldn't mind running normals to gear up for heroics <i>as long as I don't have to deal with 30+ minute wait times</i> as DPS. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sep 23rd 2010 10:02pm by Lyrailis </span></i></div>
