      <div class="msgContentFrame">As I see it, there were only two problems with tBC heroics: <br /> <br />1) Slightly overtuned in terms of gear in one or two places (e.g. the bog lords just before the black stalker0. <br /> <br />2) Getting the rep for some of the keys were a pain. <br /> <br />With a few scant exceptions Wrath heroics were just as brainless as normal modes and incredibly dull; they obviated the point of heroics in the first place, as normals were never required or even especially beneficial to beat them (so you might as well have had a single tier system). Yeah, not even for tanks. Also robs people unable to raid of a sense of progression and gives them effectively less content.  <br /> <br />No keys, or keys that require honoured, in a system otherwise like tBC and I would be happy. tBC heroics were puggable - I pugged them - but I can see why you'd actually want to check the person you bring along is capable of speech first. That does take away from the LFG tool, but I hate the LFG tool* so, really, I don't mind. <br /> <br />Honestly, though, we have fewer dungeons in Cata than in WLK or tBC (the number of launch instances per exp has steadily declined) and I doubt getting keys would be a big deal. It's just not an issue I care about either way. I think a better attunement might be forcing people to run the instance once on normal. <br /> <br /><span class="sm">* It diminishes the sense of world important to an MMO (so do other things, but generally with better reason), talks sh*t to you about what gear you have to have, diminishes the sense of server community and makes it harder to set up groups that aren't full of the people you tend to get through it. I am not a gear elitist except where you have to be, but I prefer the people I run with not to be... look, I'm rambling; I assume everyone knows how the people you meet in LFG talk and act.</span> <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>How to play the Cameron drinking game: every time David Cameron is elected Prime Minister you drink for five years. <br /> <br />Koalotter buoyed by Kirby.</div></div>
