      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">ElMuneco wrote:</div><div class="orig">But the first time I'm kicked from a dungeon queue, or eliminated from consideration for &quot;prime&quot; instances because, while waiting, I switched to <a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?witem=33820" rel="external nofollow" title="wow.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?witem=33820">Weather-Beaten Fishing Hat</a> and <a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?witem=45858" rel="external" title="wow.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?witem=45858">Nat's Lucky Fishing Pole</a>, someone's going to get a harshly worded letter...</div></div> <br /> <br />It's a pretty simple thing to cover.  The in-game gear checker does it's thing 1 minute into an instance, and gives you the opportunity to swap the gear and move on.  It would even be a handy reminder for folks who are still using their Horde/Alliance Lances from the Tournament if something like it is included in the Cata instances.  If you were able to que in the first place, you ought to be given the opportunity to rectify any gear-swapping since then.  It's really just a way of preventing folks from queing as a tank with their DPS setup and then not being able to actually tank when they switch specs.  I don't know of any easy way to have the LFD tool check for spec/gear, cuz there's enough times where folks will do stuff as an alternate role for outside the instance while waiting for the que.  I just don't want to carry another heirloom-wearing hunter through ICC25 (did this just last night,) or a fresh 80 through HHoR.  It's not like it's possible for the game to check your skill-level. <br /> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Lyrailis wrote:</div><div class="orig">Maybe if you had a &quot;One Rep Fits All&quot;, maybe. <br /> <br />But, if you require everyone to do Normals to get into Heroics, we'd have a repeat of TBC, where a newcomer who's &quot;Late to the Party&quot;, you end up with a similar situation: Sitting in LFD for 30min+ trying to get a dungeon. <br /> <br />That is just not fun at all, in the least. Nobody should be punished for arriving late, and/or trying to gear up an alt.</div></div> <br /> <br />I've been able to hit Honored and a half with Thrallmar just by doing LFD instances and very little questing.  If I can do it when I'm only doing the instances as often as I get randomly qued for them, then others can do the same thing.  Revered is not hard...and with the LFG tool in the game in the first place, there's almost no excuse to not be able to get that rep.  There are -always- people doing those dungeons.  With questing, I could probably hit Revered in a couple hours.  Again, too, this is Thrallmar rep, not some screwy minor thing that's hard to find +rep for.  Instances never ought to be tied to reputations that are difficult to get credit with, and I say it should only be Revered because it's moderately challenging to get (instances+questing over the course of normal leveling activities,) but not nearly so bad as getting Exalted (instances+questing+a month of your life where you get no benefit.)   <br /> <br />&quot;Showing up late&quot; would have absolutely no affect on this.  I pulled my warlock out of retirement once a little while ago, and his end-game raiding gear from BC was better than 95% of the drops up through regular Frozen Halls, so I didn't use any of it.  When I hit 80 and the time came to start doing the easier Heroics, I had to drop money on crafted gear because I couldn't take the hit on instance drops that were actually worse, but had a higher item level, so I could actually que for the most basic and easy of those Heroics instances.  I hadn't played my lock since Wrath came out, so you could easily call him a late-comer.  I'm not easily able to get into Heroics.  All I had to do was pay a little attention. <br /></div>
