      <div class="msgContentFrame">I think they need to find a happy medium.  Wrath was so quick and so fast that you also had people, because they were relatively easy, trying to enter them with little to no prep.  Tanks were required to be at 'Def Cap', but DPS (Especially ranged) and healers had few, if any formal numbers they had to hit. <br /> <br />My worry is that now, as &quot;Def-Capping&quot; is no longer going to be a &quot;Gearing up&quot; - you might find tanks, wholly  unprepared, claiming they are at “Def-Cap” due to talents – and thus ready to enter heroics.  (As I recall it, the question – from a tank’s perspective, “Am I ready for heroics” was generally answered as “Are you Def-Capped?”  A response of “YES” meant you were good to go as achieving Def-cap generally assured you picked up enough STA, STR, etc as additional stats on the armor. <br /> <br />It’s almost as if the problem with heroics that pissed me off the most (unprepared people entering and F’ing up the group) is now being institutionalized across the board. <br /> <br />*Please note – Now-a-days, with my Alt tank running in all T9 and some T10 gear, you could probably drag a completely naked DPS, (With Rez Sickness) through any one of the Heroics (Barring the ICC stuff)…  But when Wrath launched, it seemed like any idiot with an 80 and 1 blue piece of Quest Gear could hop into a group… <br /> <br />I spend hours grinding rep to get a stupid shoulder enchant – which I’m going to need to do a heroic….  Only to show up and realize there’s not lock on the door…  The idiot healing me just dinged 80 yesterday and is wearing ½ quest greens and his trinkets are 4 levels out of date. <br /> <br />It just seems to me to be a bit reversed.  The stupid shoulder thing took days and days to grind out.  Getting the rep, then dropping the G to buy it.  But so long as you’re 80, all the heroics are open.  I’d really like to see them put some reasonable locks on the doors.   <br /> <br />I don’t want to revert to the old days, but the wrath method of letting everyone into the party…  well it just didn’t work. <br /> <br /><i>There’s a reason they make doctors take Organic Chemistry – it has nothing to do with Doctoring… But it’s a high enough hurdle that it keeps most of the morons out…</i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Most things you worry about never happen anyway.</div></div>
