      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">xorq wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">yossarian wrote:</div><div class="orig">I have no problem with heroic versions of dungeons being so hard I won't see them. <br /> <br />I would like some kind of smooth ascension of difficulty level.  Perhaps I'll get to level 85 reg dungeons and stay there for a while.  Or perhaps the first couple of heroics would be OK. <br /> <br />I hope that the reward (justice points? conquest points?) has some kind of sliding scale rather then all heroics being equal.</div></div> <br /> <br />That part has already been defined. <br /> <br />Heroics give and lower tier raids give heroic tier points. I think they will also have a daily random and weekly giving raid tier points in small amounts the same way we get frost emblems now. <br /> <br />And raids give raid tier points. <br /> <br />And long ago they decided they didn't like having made content so difficult to reach that it excludes a large portion of people from engaging in it. They want all content to be within reach of everyone assuming you learn to play.</div></div> <br /> <br />So I think you are saying it has been defined that all heroic versions of 5-man content gives equal points? <br /> <br />I was saying I have no issue with some heroics being harder then others and thus giving more points. <br /> <br />Optimally, I thought, there would be a sliding scale of difficulty.  Just to have arbitrary numbers, say 80 points for a reg level 85 dungeon, 110 points for (say) the easiest 3 heroics, 165 points for the next tier of (say) 3 heroics, and the hardest ones giving 200 points. <br /> <br />Why?  Partly, as a very part time player, I think I could nail down 5 instances and bang a random button, knowing OK I'm getting a lower reward but it is only 5 of them. <br /> <br />Further, all of us would be able to see all dungeon content (so long as we agree most of us who are competent can get through 5-mans on reg. difficulty) and it would make reg. mode useful. <br /> <br />Now you might say, well I'm going to master all heroics and I want max points for them all.  Fine.  I have no issue with you getting to a point where you can do that.  Even if we wind up in the same group (I've checked the box indicating I'm prepared only for the first 3 heroics, let's say, and you have all open) and I end up with, say, 110 points and you get 200.  It is unlikely you'll need any of the gear drops and I'm getting a faster run for you being there. <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><i><span class="sm">Do the right thing.</span></i> <br /></div></div>
