      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">So I think you are saying it has been defined that all heroic versions of 5-man content gives equal points? <br /> <br />I was saying I have no issue with some heroics being harder then others and thus giving more points. <br /></div></div> <br /> <br />Points are handed per kill, not per dungeon. Each different optional miniboss or different boss can give a different amount, much like exp or gold. <br /> <br />If the week limit was 200, and you can do full clears of the hardest dungeons that give the most points you'll get to 200, and if you can do 20 bad runs that dissolve before completing the run and give 10 points each you'll get your 200 too. The 5-man tier doesn't have &quot;<i>but I am better and I deserve more</i>&quot;, if you're better you'll suffer less to get your points. <br /> <br />The weekly limit is also going to be there for raid tiers. So instead of having to do 7 heroics, 1 raid weekly quest, a 25 man icc and a 10 man icc for your full weekly quota of frosts you'll instead be doing your raid only and you don't need to be adding any extra quests or heroics to reach the full weekly quota, unless your raid isn't deep enough in proggress so that you'd need to add some points from the lower tiers. <br /> <br />There's still going to be like 4 to 8 random drops per dungeon run which have a chance to give an instant upgrade without any points. And there's going to be more crafted BoEs too. So I'm expecting that the gearing process isn't going to be so much of a chore as it has been until now, so you probably will be more worried about how to confront the content instead of about how to get the gear. <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>NOTE: I may post comments about my like/dislike/approval/disapproval of game features. <br />1- They are NOT a complaint. They are a perspective. <br />2- They are NOT advocacy. They are a perspective.</div></div>
